b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Adobe Podcast is best suited for cleaning up audio recordings, podcast creators in Adobe ecosystem, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Riverside, meanwhile, shines for remote podcast recording, high quality interviews, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Adobe Podcast describes itself as \"AI-powered audio recording and enhancement by Adobe.\" Riverside, established in 2019, positions itself as \"Studio-quality recordings from anywhere.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Riverside** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (4 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Adobe Podcast is a poor choice — far from it. Adobe Podcast excels in its own right, particularly for cleaning up audio recordings and podcast creators in Adobe ecosystem.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value local recording for max quality, go with Riverside. If excellent enhance speech feature matters more to you, Adobe Podcast is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
